# EXPERIMENT EXECUTION

## Launching Is NOT Task Completion

**The workflow is: Launch → Monitor → Analyze → Propose → Loop**

## Monitoring (Context-Efficient)

**DO NOT use `tail -f` — it floods context.**

```bash
# Option 1: Background monitor (preferred — only outputs on metric changes)
./scripts/monitor.sh --log logs/train_r<N>.log --pid $(cat logs/train.pid) --interval 120

# Option 2: Sparse polling
grep -E "(loss|epoch|val_)" logs/train_r<N>.log | tail -3

# Option 3: SLURM
squeue -j <job_id> -h -o "%T %M"
```

## Early Stopping Heuristics

**Compare current run against baselines in findings.md:**

| Training % | STOP if | CONTINUE if |
|------------|---------|-------------|
| First 100 steps | Loss NaN/Inf/increasing | Steady decrease |
| ~5% | Loss >5x baseline at same point | Within 2x of baseline |
| ~10% | Val metric flat or random-level | Trending up, even slowly |
| ~25% | Significantly below baseline curve | Comparable to baseline |
| ~50% | Plateaued well below baseline | On track to match/beat |

```bash
# Compare current vs baseline
grep -E "val_" logs/train_r<N>.log | tail -3
cat doc/agent/findings.md | grep -A5 "Baseline"
```

## After Round Completes (or Early Stops)

**You are in a LOOP. Do NOT stop here.**

1. Record result in results.tsv
2. Write analysis in doc/agent/exp_r\<N\>.md (diagnose why it worked/failed)
3. Update findings.md with new patterns
4. Propose next round (or exit loop if done)
5. Update sketch.md

**Exit loop when:** target achieved, hypotheses exhausted, or user stops.

